-- Gurit, Nestle, Richemont, Swatch: Swiss Equity Preview
-- B y   A l e x i s   X y d i a s
-- 2010-09-21T06:46:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/gurit-nestle-richemont-swatch-may-move-in-zurich-swiss-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Zurich. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names. Prices are from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies rose 1.1 percent to 6,461.98 in Zurich. The
broader  Swiss Performance Index  increased 1.1 percent to
5,706.08.       Cie. Financiere Richemont SA  (CFR VX), Switzerland’s
largest jewelry maker and  Swatch Group AG  (UHR VX), the maker of
Omega and Breguet watches: Swiss watch exports rose 24.1 percent
in August, the Federal Customs Offices said today in an e-mailed
statement. Richemont rose 2.9 percent to 45.1 francs. Swatch
gained 3.1 percent to 363.3 francs.       Gurit Holding AG  (GUR SW): The company said it had earnings
before interest and taxes of 13.3 million francs in the first
half and that it sees stronger profit in the second half. The
shares lost 3.7 percent to 524 francs.       Nestle SA  (NESN VX): The company is employing marketing
methods developed for emerging markets such as Russia and
Thailand to increase sales in ailing European economies such as
Greece, Spain and Ireland, the Financial Times reported, citing
 Laurent Freixe , the company’s Europe chief. Nestle shares rose
1.3 percent to 52.80 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
